(356, 1, '2013-01-13 12:03:28', '2013-01-13 00:03:28', '<div class="gallery"><a class="fancybox" title="Comments made on facebook would appear on live TV." href="http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/ulive-screen1.jpg" rel="gallery1"><img class="size-thumbnail wp-image-338 " alt="Ulive comments page" src="http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/ulive-screen1-200x200.jpg" width="200" height="200" /></a><a class="fancybox" title="Facebook users could vote in polls which would be discussed by the presenters" href="http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/ulive-screen2.jpg" rel="gallery1"><img class="size-thumbnail wp-image-339 " alt="Ulive voting page " src="http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/ulive-screen2-200x200.jpg" width="200" height="200" /></a><a class="fancybox" title="Facebook users could stream Ulive from within the app" href="http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/ulive-screen3.jpg" rel="gallery1"><img class="size-thumbnail wp-image-340 " alt="Ulive streaming page" src="http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/ulive-screen3-200x200.jpg" width="200" height="200" /></a><a class="fancybox" title="Users could invite their friends to take part in the discussions" href="http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/ulive-screen4.jpg" rel="gallery1"><img class="size-thumbnail wp-image-341 " alt="Ulive invite page" src="http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/ulive-screen4-200x200.jpg" width="200" height="200" /></a></div>\r\n<h2>Purpose</h2>\r\nThe goal of this project was to create a Facebook app housed on the TVNZU page which allowed facebook users to watch the live show. It was to allow the users to get involved in the discussions the presenters were having and even get their comments to appear in real time on live TV. It was also to create a sense of community within the users friends by allowing them to invite their friends to watch the show and also display a list of which of your friends were currently tuned in via the app.\r\n<h2>Technology</h2>\r\nThis project was built on the Zend Framework and implements the Facebook API, JQuery, AJAX and a custom scroll bar JS library.\r\n<h2>Challenge</h2>\r\nGetting all these technologies to integrate seamlessly\r\n<h2>Method</h2>\r\nThis project was built on the Zend Framework and implements the Facebook API, JQuery, AJAX and a custom scroll bar JS library.\r\n<h2>Results</h2>\r\nThis project was built on the Zend Framework and implements the Facebook API, JQuery, AJAX and a custom scroll bar JS library.', 'Ulive', 'This project encompassed a wide range of web technologies. It was the first facebook app to allow users to interact with live television and was featured on facebook''s developer blog.', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '337-revision-14', '', '', '2013-01-13 12:03:28', '2013-01-13 00:03:28', '', 337, 'http://localhost/techblog/articles/337-revision-14/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
