(462, 1, '2013-01-16 20:14:51', '2013-01-16 08:14:51', '<div class="gallery"><a class="fancybox" title="Users could take a picture using their webcam" href="http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/doggelganger-screen1.jpg" rel="gallery1"><img class="size-thumbnail wp-image-338 " alt="Doggelganger Webcam" src="http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/doggelganger-screen1-200x200.jpg" width="200" height="200" /></a><a class="fancybox" title="The site used NEC facial recognition software to scan the users facial features" href="http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/doggelganger-screen2.jpg" rel="gallery1"><img class="size-thumbnail wp-image-339 " alt="Doggelganger Image Processing" src="http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/doggelganger-screen2-200x200.jpg" width="200" height="200" /></a><a class="fancybox" title="NEC''s results were used to pair the user with a dog from the SPCA" href="http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/doggelganger-screen3.jpg" rel="gallery1"><img class="size-thumbnail wp-image-340 " alt="Doggelganger Results" src="http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/doggelganger-screen3-200x200.jpg" width="200" height="200" /></a><a class="fancybox" title="Users could share their results on Facebook" href="http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/doggelganger-screen4.jpg" rel="gallery1"><img class="size-thumbnail wp-image-341 " alt="Doggelganger Share " src="http://localhost/techblog/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/doggelganger-screen4-200x200.jpg" width="200" height="200" /></a></div>\r\n<h3>Goals</h3>\r\nThis project aimed to create a website which users could upload their photo to and get their face matched to a dog which is up for adoption at the SPCA. The premise being that owners often look like their pets.\r\n<h3>Technology</h3>\r\nThis project was built in Flash with the CMS and API built on the Zend Framework. It also implements the Facebook and NEC APIs.\r\n<h3